JOHANNESBURG - Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng has declined to meet with human rights organisation Africa4Palestine over his anti-Palestine and pro-Israeli comments. During a webinar last year hosted by the Jerusalem Post, Mogoeng quoted from the Bible, saying that he was praying for Israel and pledged his love for the country. READ: Mogoeng ordered to retract & apologise for Israel-Palestine conflict comments Earlier this month, the Judicial Service Commission ruled that Mogoeng was in breach of its service and ordered him to retract his remarks. ALSO READ: Mogoeng set to appeal JCC decision on his Israel-Palestine conflict comments Africa4Palestine approached the commission to take steps against the Chief Justice and he was ordered to apologise. However, Mogoeng decided to lodge an appeal against the commission's ruling. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.